kernel_variant.question:
Let  
\[
S=\Bigl\{x=(x_{1},\dots ,x_{6})\in\mathbb R^{6}\;\Bigm|\;
x_{i}\ge 0,\;
\sum_{i=1}^{6}x_{i}=12,\;
\sum_{i=1}^{6}x_{i}^{2}=30\Bigr\},
\qquad
H=\Bigl\{y=(y_{1},\dots ,y_{6})\in\mathbb R^{6}\;\Bigm|\;
y_{1}=y_{2}=y_{3}=s>0,\;
y_{4}=y_{5}=y_{6}=t>0,\;
s>t,\;
st=9\Bigr\}.
\]

For \(x\in S\) and \(y\in H\) denote the squared Euclidean distance by  
\[
D(x,y)=\bigl\lVert x-y\bigr\rVert^{2}=\sum_{i=1}^{6}(x_{i}-y_{i})^{2}.
\]

(A) Prove that  
\[
D_{\min}:=\min\bigl\{D(x,y):x\in S,\;y\in H\bigr\}
\]
is attained.

(B) Determine \(D_{\min}\) in exact closed form (expressions by radicals over \(\mathbb Q\) are required) and describe \emph{all} pairs \((x,y)\) that realise this minimum.

